## 🔒 Security

### Package Verification

All release artifacts are signed and can be verified:

```bash
# Download checksums and signature
wget https://github.com/ghuntley/cursed/releases/download/v{{VERSION}}/SHA256SUMS
wget https://github.com/ghuntley/cursed/releases/download/v{{VERSION}}/SHA256SUMS.sig

# Import GPG key (first time only)
gpg --recv-keys 0x1234567890ABCDEF

# Verify signature
gpg --verify SHA256SUMS.sig SHA256SUMS

# Verify your download
sha256sum -c SHA256SUMS
```

### Container Image Verification

```bash
# Verify container image signatures
docker trust inspect cursed/compiler:{{VERSION}}

# Run security scan
docker scout cves cursed/compiler:{{VERSION}}
```

## 🚀 Quick Start

### Hello World

```bash
# Create a simple program
echo 'vibez.spill("Hello, CURSED!")' > hello.💀

# Run it
cursed-zig hello.💀
```

### Using the Standard Library

```cursed
yeet "mathz"
yeet "stringz"

sus result drip = add_numbers(21, 21)
sus message tea = format_string("Answer: {}", [result])
vibez.spill(message)
```

### LSP Integration

The Language Server Protocol (LSP) server provides IDE integration:

```bash
# Start LSP server for VS Code, Vim, etc.
cursed-lsp --stdio
```

## 🔧 Configuration

### Environment Variables

- `CURSED_CACHE_DIR`: Compiler cache directory (default: `~/.cursed/cache`)
- `CURSED_STDLIB_PATH`: Standard library path (auto-detected)
- `CURSED_PARALLEL_JOBS`: Number of parallel compilation jobs
- `CURSED_OPTIMIZATION_LEVEL`: Default optimization level (0-3)

### Configuration File

Create `~/.cursed/config.toml`:

```toml
[compiler]
optimization_level = 2
parallel_jobs = 4
cache_enabled = true

[lsp]
port = 9999
host = "127.0.0.1"
log_level = "info"

[paths]
stdlib = "/usr/local/share/cursed/stdlib"
cache = "~/.cursed/cache"
```

